question:
District category contains Wall Street, and Colonial District.
Supermarkets category contains Walmart, and Fresh Thyme Market.
Product category contains Plant-based Yogurt, and Fruit Snacks.
Ingredient category contains Olive Oil, and Chocolate Chips.
The number of each Colonial District 's Walmart equals 7 more than the difference of each Fruit Snacks 's Chocolate Chips and each Fresh Thyme Market 's Plant-based Yogurt.
The number of each Plant-based Yogurt 's Olive Oil equals 2 times each Fresh Thyme Market 's Fruit Snacks.
The number of each Fruit Snacks 's Chocolate Chips equals 6 more than each Fresh Thyme Market 's Plant-based Yogurt.
The number of each Walmart 's Plant-based Yogurt equals the sum of each Fruit Snacks 's Chocolate Chips, each Colonial District 's Supermarkets, and each Fresh Thyme Market 's Product.
The number of each Wall Street 's Walmart equals 21 times each Fresh Thyme Market 's Fruit Snacks.
The number of each Fruit Snacks 's Olive Oil equals each Fresh Thyme Market 's Fruit Snacks.
The number of each Fresh Thyme Market 's Plant-based Yogurt equals 20.
The number of each Fresh Thyme Market 's Fruit Snacks equals 13.
How many Plant-based Yogurt does Fresh Thyme Market have?
solution: Define each Fresh Thyme Market 's Plant-based Yogurt as j; So j = 20.
